The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for stereo matching, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed pipeline involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which are also commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper introduces a new technique for training the network, which involves a reflective loss, which could potentially fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Lastly, the paper mentions the use of the pipeline for robotic applications, which could fall under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
